{"parse":{"title":"Why I Am A Hindu","pageid":57504333,"revid":854162320,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Why I Am A Hindu <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Why+I+Am+A+Hindu&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BShashi+Tharoor%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=19+January+2018&amp;rft.pub=Aleph+Book+Company&amp;rft.pages=320\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Tharoor_WhyIAmAHindu.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Tharoor WhyIAmAHindu.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Tharoor_WhyIAmAHindu.jpg/220px-Tharoor_WhyIAmAHindu.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"327\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/6c/Tharoor_WhyIAmAHindu.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"223\" data-file-height=\"331\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Shashi_Tharoor\" title=\"Shashi Tharoor\">Shashi Tharoor</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\nAleph Book Company</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n19 January 2018</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nPrint (hardcover)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n320</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-9386021106\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-9386021106\">978-9386021106</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Why I Am A Hindu</b></i> is a 2018 book by Indian politician <a href=\"/wiki/Shashi_Tharoor\" title=\"Shashi Tharoor\">Shashi Tharoor</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> In the book, Tharoor writes about the history of <a href=\"/wiki/Hinduism\" title=\"Hinduism\">Hinduism</a> and its core tenets, as well as socio-cultural developments in India that relate to the religion, while elucidating his own religious convictions.\n</p><p>Tharoor intended the book to be a repudiation of Hindu nationalism, and its rise in Indian society, which relied upon an interpretation of the religion which was markedly different from the one with which he had grown up, and was familiar with. In seeking to address this concern, he wanted to position the debate as one within the Hindu faith, and therefore wrote about his own personal identification with the religion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>The book is segmented into two parts. In the first part, Tharoor offers a brief history of Hinduism, and the development of his own personal faith. In the second part, he traces the rise of modern Hindu nationalism in the form of the <a href=\"/wiki/Hindutva\" title=\"Hindutva\">Hindutva</a> movement.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Why_I_Am_A_Hindu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Chanda-Vaz, Urmi (2018-02-18). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scroll.in/article/868932/shashi-tharoors-why-i-am-a-hindu-is-a-timely-reminder-of-why-hinduism-must-retain-its-pluralism\">\"Shashi Tharoor's 'Why I Am A Hindu' is a timely reminder of why Hinduism must retain its pluralism\"</a>. <i>Scroll.in</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-05-24</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Scroll.in&amp;rft.atitle=Shashi+Tharoor%E2%80%99s+%E2%80%98Why+I+Am+A+Hindu%E2%80%99+is+a+timely+reminder+of+why+Hinduism+must+retain+its+pluralism&amp;rft.date=2018-02-18&amp;rft.aulast=Chanda-Vaz&amp;rft.aufirst=Urmi&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F868932%2Fshashi-tharoors-why-i-am-a-hindu-is-a-timely-reminder-of-why-hinduism-must-retain-its-pluralism&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWhy+I+Am+A+Hindu\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Daniyal, Shoaib (2018-02-11). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scroll.in/article/868126/i-want-to-resist-the-hijacking-of-hinduism-by-hindutva-the-shashi-tharoor-interview\">\"I want to resist the hijacking of Hinduism by Hindutva: The Shashi Tharoor interview\"</a>. <i>Scroll.in</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-05-25</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Scroll.in&amp;rft.atitle=I+want+to+resist+the+hijacking+of+Hinduism+by+Hindutva%3A+The+Shashi+Tharoor+interview&amp;rft.date=2018-02-11&amp;rft.aulast=Daniyal&amp;rft.aufirst=Shoaib&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F868126%2Fi-want-to-resist-the-hijacking-of-hinduism-by-hindutva-the-shashi-tharoor-interview&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWhy+I+Am+A+Hindu\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=